# Architecture Diagrams
Below are two complementary architectural views: a Deployment diagram (Containers and Network) and a Sequence diagram (Event Flow and Actuation).

## Deployment & Component Diagram
This diagram illustrates the microservices infrastructure within the isolated Docker network (mars_network). It shows the physical decoupling between modules and the ports exposed to the host.

flowchart TB
    subgraph "External Environment"
        Simulator["Mars IoT Simulator\n(Sensors & Actuators)"]
    end

    subgraph "Data Ingestion & Messaging"
        Ingestion["Ingestion Service\n(Polls Simulator)"]
        Broker["RabbitMQ\n(Message Broker)"]
    end

    subgraph "Automation Engine (FastAPI)"
        BrokerClient["broker.py\n(RabbitMQ Consumer)"]
        RuleLogic["logic.py & state.py\n(Rule Evaluation & State)"]
        DBManager["db.py\n(SQLite Settings)"]
        API["engine.py\n(REST API Endpoints)"]
        
        BrokerClient -->|"Telemetry Data"| RuleLogic
        RuleLogic <-->|"Read/Check Rules"| DBManager
        API <-->|"Manage Rules/Get State"| RuleLogic
        API <-->|"CRUD Rules"| DBManager
    end

    subgraph "Storage"
        SQLite[("rules.db\n(SQLite)")]
    end

    subgraph "User Interface"
        Frontend["Frontend Dashboard\n(React/Next.js)"]
    end

    %% External Connections
    Simulator -- "HTTP GET\nSensor Data" --> Ingestion
    Ingestion -- "AMQP Publish" --> Broker
    Broker -- "AMQP Consume" --> BrokerClient
    
    RuleLogic -- "HTTP POST\nActuator Commands" --> Simulator
    
    DBManager <--> SQLite
    
    Frontend <-->|"HTTP GET / POST / DELETE\n(Manage Rules, Live Status)"| API
    
